6-Week DSA Learning Plan
Week 1: Arrays, Strings & Time Complexity
Topics to Cover:
Big O notation (time and space complexity)
Array manipulation techniques
String operations
Basic problem-solving patterns
Reading Materials:
GeeksforGeeks: Big O notation
GeeksforGeeks: Arrays in Python
GeeksforGeeks: String manipulation
LeetCode Explore: Arrays 101
Video Resources:
freeCodeCamp "Algorithms and Data Structures" (first 2 hours)
NeetCode "Big O Notation Explained"
NeetCode "Arrays & Hashing" playlist
Practice Problems (LeetCode):
Two Sum (Easy)
Best Time to Buy and Sell Stock (Easy)
Contains Duplicate (Easy)
Valid Anagram (Easy)
Reverse String (Easy)
Product of Array Except Self (Medium)
Daily Study Pattern:
Morning (1 hour):

Read GeeksforGeeks article (20 min)
Watch video (30 min)
Review yesterday's notes (10 min)
Evening (1.5-2 hours):

Solve 2 problems
First attempt without help (30 min each)
If stuck, watch solution then code yourself
Write down patterns learned
Week Goal:
Solve 12-15 problems, understand Big O thoroughly

