Week 5: Recursion, Backtracking & Dynamic Programming
Topics to Cover:
Recursion fundamentals
Backtracking patterns
Introduction to Dynamic Programming
Memoization
Bottom-up vs top-down approaches
Reading Materials:
GeeksforGeeks: Recursion
GeeksforGeeks: Backtracking
GeeksforGeeks: Dynamic Programming introduction
GeeksforGeeks: Memoization
Video Resources:
Abdul Bari "Recursion" playlist
NeetCode "Dynamic Programming" beginner videos
freeCodeCamp "Dynamic Programming" section
Practice Problems:
Recursion:

Fibonacci Number (Easy)
Climbing Stairs (Easy)
Power(x, n) (Medium)
Backtracking: 4. Subsets (Medium) 5. Permutations (Medium) 6. Combination Sum (Medium)

Dynamic Programming: 7. House Robber (Medium) 8. Coin Change (Medium) 9. Longest Increasing Subsequence (Medium)

Key Technique:
For each DP problem:

Solve with recursion first
Add memoization
Convert to bottom-up if possible
Draw recursion tree
Week Goal:
Solve 12-14 problems, understand DP basics

