Problem-Solving Framework (Use Every Time)
The 7-Step Approach:
Understand: Read problem 2-3 times, clarify inputs/outputs
Example: Work through example manually on paper
Approach: Think brute force first, then optimize
Pseudocode: Write steps before coding
Code: Implement solution
Test: Run with edge cases (empty, single element, duplicates)
Optimize: Can you improve time/space complexity?
When Stuck (30-minute rule):
Struggle for 30 minutes trying different approaches
If still stuck, look at hints only
If still stuck after hints, watch solution explanation
Always code the solution yourself after watching
Come back to the problem in 3 days
