Best Study Approach (For All Learning)
The Learning Cycle:
Read/Watch tutorial to understand concept
Code Along while learning (type everything)
Build the same thing without looking
Reference docs when stuck
Repeat with next topic
Daily Study Routine:
Morning (1-2 hours):

Read tutorial/documentation (20-30 min)
Watch corresponding video (30-40 min)
Take notes on key concepts (10 min)
Evening (2-3 hours):

Code along with tutorial (1 hour)
Build same feature from scratch (1 hour)
Debug and reference docs (30 min)
Weekend:

Build mini projects
Experiment and break things
Review week's material
Key Principles:
‚úÖ DO THIS:

Small cycles: learn ‚Üí practice ‚Üí build
Type every line of code yourself
Apply immediately after learning
Struggle before looking for help
Draw diagrams and visualize
Explain concepts out loud
‚ùå DON'T DO THIS:

Watch multiple tutorials without coding
Copy-paste code without understanding
Give up too quickly
Skip "easy" topics
Just read without implementing
Using Documentation Effectively
Documentation is NOT a textbook:
Don't read cover-to-cover
Use as a reference/dictionary
Search for specific topics when needed
Bookmark frequently used pages
How to Use Docs:
Start with tutorial sections (read like a book)
After tutorials, use docs for lookup only
When stuck while coding ‚Üí search docs ‚Üí read that section only
Bookmark most-referenced pages
Most-Referenced Django Docs:
Models reference
QuerySet API reference
DRF Serializers reference
Authentication guide
Practice Exercise:
After Django tutorial:

Pick a feature (e.g., "file uploads")
Search Django docs for it
Read ONLY that page
Implement in test project
Repeat with different features
Within a month, docs become your natural first stop for questions

